item.title: Help D':
item.dc:creator: @tobias222 tobias222
item.description:
@tobias222 wrote:

Yes, I would say use a better host.
I had this problem a few times and uploading a large .zip file on bad hosts can cause corruption within the archive, also may be to do with the poor downloading quality when your users download it.
This error is also known to be caused by the client being unable to access the background image from the path in class30_sub2_sub1_sub1.java, although I would say the problem with yours is simply that it is uploaded to a poor host, going by the file sizes of the partially-downloaded cache.
